g1502.definition: [εἴκω] apparently a primary verb; properly, to be weak, i.e. yield

g1503.definition: [εἴκω] apparently a primary verb (perhaps akin to {{g1502}} through the idea of faintness as a copy); to resemble

g1504.definition: [εἰκών] from {{g1503}}; a likeness, i.e. (literally) statue, profile, or (figuratively) representation, resemblance

g1506.definition: [εἰλικρινής] from εἵλη (the sun's ray) and {{g2919}}; judged by sunlight, i.e. tested as genuine (figuratively)

g1507.definition: [εἱλίσσω] a prolonged form of a primary but defective verb εἵλω (of the same meaning); to coil or wrap See also {{g1667}}.

g1509.definition: [εἰ μή τι] from {{g1508}} and the neuter of {{g5100}}; if not somewhat

g1510.definition: [εἰμί] the first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist (used only when emphatic) See also {{g1488}}, {{g1498}}, {{g1511}}, {{g1526}}, {{g2258}}, {{g2071}}, {{g2070}}, {{g2075}}, {{g2076}}, {{g2771}}, {{g2468}}, {{g5600}}.

g1511.definition: [εἶναι] present infinitive from {{g1510}}; to exist come, is, X lust after, X please well, there is, to be, was.

g1515.definition: [εἰρήνη] probably from a primary verb εἴρω (to join); peace (literally or figuratively); by implication, prosperity

g1517.definition: [εἰρηνοποιέω] from {{g1518}}; to be a peace-maker, i.e. (figuratively) to harmonize

g1519.definition: [εἰς] a primary preposition; to or into (indicating the point reached or entered), of place, time, or (figuratively) purpose (result, etc.); also in adverbial phrases Often used in composition with the same general import, but only with verbs (etc.) expressing motion (literally or figuratively).

g1520.definition: [εἷς]  (including the neuter (etc.) hen);  a primary numeral; one See also {{g1527}}, {{g3367}}, {{g3391}}, {{g3762}}.

g1521.definition: [εἰσάγω] from {{g1519}} and {{g71}}; to introduce (literally or figuratively)

g1523.definition: [εἰσδέχομαι] from {{g1519}} and {{g1209}}; to take into one's favor

g1524.definition: [εἴσειμι] from {{g1519}} and εἶμι (to go); to enter

g1525.definition: [εἰσέρχομαι] from {{g1519}} and {{g2064}}; to enter (literally or figuratively)

g1526.definition: [εἰσί] 3rd person plural present indicative of {{g1510}}; they are

g1527.definition: [εἷς καθ’ εἷς] from {{g1520}} repeated with {{g2596}} inserted; severally

g1529.definition: [εἴσοδος] from {{g1519}} and {{g3598}}; an entrance (literally or figuratively)

g1530.definition: [εἰσπηδάω] from {{g1519}} and πηδάω (to leap); to rush in

g1531.definition: [εἰσπορεύομαι] from {{g1519}} and {{g4198}}; to enter (literally or figuratively)

g1533.definition: [εἰσφέρω] from {{g1519}} and {{g5342}}; to carry inward (literally or figuratively)

g1534.definition: [εἶτα] of uncertain affinity; a particle of succession (in time or logical enumeration), then, moreover See also {{g1899}}.

g1537.definition: [ἐκ]   or ἐξa primary preposition denoting origin (the point whence action or motion proceeds), from, out (of place, time, or cause; literal or figurative; direct or remote) Often used in composition, with the same general import; often of completion.

g1538.definition: [ἕκαστος] as if a superlative of ἕκας (afar); each or every

g1539.definition: [ἑκάστοτε] as if from {{g1538}} and {{g5119}}; at every time

g1542.definition: [ἑκατονταπλασίων] from {{g1540}} and a presumed derivative of {{g4111}}; a hundred times

g1543.definition: [ἑκατοντάρχης]   or ἑκατόνταρχοςfrom {{g1540}} and {{g757}}; the captain of one hundred men

g1544.definition: [ἐκβάλλω] from {{g1537}} and {{g906}}; to eject (literally or figuratively)

g1545.definition: [ἔκβασις] from a compound of {{g1537}} and the base of {{g939}} (meaning to go out); an exit (literally or figuratively)

g1546.definition: [ἐκβολή] from {{g1544}}; ejection, i.e. (specially) a throwing overboard of the cargo

g1547.definition: [ἐκγαμίζω] from {{g1537}} and a form of {{g1061}} (compare {{g1548}}); to marry off a daughter

g1549.definition: [ἔκγονον] neuter of a derivative of a compound of {{g1537}} and {{g1096}}; a descendant, i.e. (specially) grandchild

g1550.definition: [ἐκδαπανάω] from {{g1537}} and {{g1159}}; to expend (wholly), i.e. (figuratively) exhaust

g1551.definition: [ἐκδέχομαι] from {{g1537}} and {{g1209}}; to accept from some source, i.e. (by implication) to await

g1553.definition: [ἐκδημέω] from a compound of {{g1537}} and {{g1218}}; to emigrate, i.e. (figuratively) vacate or quit

g1554.definition: [ἐκδίδωμι] from {{g1537}} and {{g1325}}; to give forth, i.e. (specially) to lease

g1555.definition: [ἐκδιηγέομαι] from {{g1537}} and a compound of {{g1223}} and {{g2233}}; to narrate through wholly

g1558.definition: [ἔκδικος] from {{g1537}} and {{g1349}}; carrying justice out, i.e. a punisher

g1559.definition: [ἐκδιώκω] from {{g1537}} and {{g1377}}; to pursue out, i.e. expel or persecute implacably

g1560.definition: [ἔκδοτος] from {{g1537}} and a derivative of {{g1325}}; given out or over, i.e. surrendered

g1562.definition: [ἐκδύω] from {{g1537}} and the base of {{g1416}}; to cause to sink out of, i.e. (specially as of clothing) to divest

g1563.definition: [ἐκεῖ] of uncertain affinity; there; by extension, thither

g1565.definition: [ἐκεῖνος] from {{g1563}}; that one (or (neuter) thing); often intensified by the article prefixed See also {{g3778}}.

g1567.definition: [ἐκζητέω] from {{g1537}} and {{g2212}}; to search out, i.e. (figuratively)investigate, crave, demand, (by Hebraism) worship

g1570.definition: [ἔκθετος] from {{g1537}} and a derivative of {{g5087}}; put out, i.e. exposed to perish

g1573.definition: [ἐκκακέω] from {{g1537}} and {{g2556}}; to be (bad or) weak, i.e. (by implication) to fail (in heart)

g1574.definition: [ἐκκεντέω] from {{g1537}} and the base of {{g2759}}; to transfix

g1576.definition: [ἐκκλείω] from {{g1537}} and {{g2808}}; to shut out (literally or figuratively)

g1577.definition: [ἐκκλησία] from a compound of {{g1537}} and a derivative of {{g2564}}; a calling out, i.e. (concretely) a popular meeting, especially a religious congregation (Jewish synagogue, or Christian community of members on earth or saints in heaven or both)

g1578.definition: [ἐκκλίνω] from {{g1537}} and {{g2827}}; to deviate, i.e. (absolutely) to shun (literally or figuratively), or (relatively) to decline (from piety)

g1579.definition: [ἐκκολυμβάω] from {{g1537}} and {{g2860}}; to escape by swimming

g1580.definition: [ἐκκομίζω] from {{g1537}} and {{g2865}}; to bear forth (to burial)

g1581.definition: [ἐκκόπτω] from {{g1537}} and {{g2875}}; to exscind; figuratively, to frustrate

g1582.definition: [ἐκκρέμαμαι] middle voice from {{g1537}} and {{g2910}}; to hang upon the lips of a speaker, i.e. listen closely

g1585.definition: [ἐκλανθάνομαι] middle voice from {{g1537}} and {{g2990}}; to be utterly oblivious of

g1586.definition: [ἐκλέγομαι] middle voice from {{g1537}} and {{g3004}} (in its primary sense); to select

g1587.definition: [ἐκλείπω] from {{g1537}} and {{g3007}}; to omit, i.e. (by implication) cease (die)

g1590.definition: [ἐκλύω] from {{g1537}} and {{g3089}}; to relax (literally or figuratively)

g1591.definition: [ἐκμάσσω] from {{g1537}} and the base of {{g3145}}; to knead out, i.e. (by analogy) to wipe dry

g1592.definition: [ἐκμυκτηρίζω] from {{g1537}} and {{g3456}}; to sneer outright at

g1593.definition: [ἐκνεύω] from {{g1537}} and {{g3506}}; (by analogy) to slip off, i.e. quietly withdraw

g1594.definition: [ἐκνήφω] from {{g1537}} and {{g3525}}; (figuratively) to rouse (oneself) out of stupor

g1595.definition: [ἑκούσιον] neuter of a derivative from {{g1635}}; voluntariness

g1596.definition: [ἑκουσίως] adverb from the same as {{g1595}}; voluntarily

g1597.definition: [ἔκπαλαι] from {{g1537}} and {{g3819}}; long ago, for a long while

g1600.definition: [ἐκπετάννυμι] from {{g1537}} and a form of {{g4072}}; to fly out, i.e. (by analogy) to extend
